{"id":328,"date":"2025-06-06T12:55:01","date_gmt":"2025-06-06T09:55:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/um.marketing\/?p=328"},"modified":"2025-06-06T14:00:15","modified_gmt":"2025-06-06T11:00:15","slug":"seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/","title":{"rendered":"SEO in the Age of AI Search: How to Optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>AI is no longer coming for search. It is already here. With Google\u2019s Search Generative Experience and Microsoft\u2019s Bing Copilot transforming the way people find and consume information, traditional SEO practices must evolve or risk becoming obsolete.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If your website is still optimized only for classic blue link rankings, you are missing out on valuable visibility in AI-powered results. To succeed in the SEO in AI era, you need to understand how these systems think, what content they prioritize, and how to structure your site for generative engines, not just ranking algorithms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This article breaks down what Google SGE and Bing Copilot are, what is changing in AI search, and how to build an AI search SEO strategy that actually gets you featured in generative summaries and AI snippets.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_68_1 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-white ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/#What_Is_Google_SGE_and_Bing_Copilot\" title=\"What Is Google SGE and Bing Copilot\">What Is Google SGE and Bing Copilot<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/#Why_SEO_Is_Changing_in_the_AI_Era\" title=\"Why SEO Is Changing in the AI Era\">Why SEO Is Changing in the AI Era<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/#How_to_Optimize_for_Google_SGE_and_Bing_Copilot\" title=\"How to Optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot\">How to Optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/#What_Not_to_Do_in_the_AI_SEO_Era\" title=\"What Not to Do in the AI SEO Era\">What Not to Do in the AI SEO Era<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/#Conclusion\" title=\"Conclusion\">Conclusion<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_Is_Google_SGE_and_Bing_Copilot\"><\/span>What Is Google SGE and Bing Copilot<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Google SGE stands for Search Generative Experience. It uses large language models to generate summarized answers directly in the search results. Instead of just showing ten blue links, Google now presents AI-generated content that pulls data from multiple sites and answers the query in a single, conversational block.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bing Copilot functions similarly. Powered by ChatGPT integration, it answers queries directly and offers clickable source citations to the websites it pulls information from.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What this means for SEO:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Traffic shifts from top ten links to featured answers and citations<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Content must be semantically rich and structured to be AI-readable<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>E E A T signals matter more, especially for queries needing expertise or accuracy<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Why_SEO_Is_Changing_in_the_AI_Era\"><\/span>Why SEO Is Changing in the AI Era<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>AI search does not just crawl and rank. It reads, summarizes, and interprets. Your content is not being listed\u2014it is being digested and rephrased. This changes how Google and Bing select what to feature.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Core differences in AI search:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Emphasis on context and relationships between topics<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Priority to content that directly answers user intent<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Need for clear headings, structured data, and factual clarity<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Heavy reliance on internal consistency and external validation (like citations)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In this landscape, content that is vague, shallow, or fragmented will be skipped over\u2014no matter how many links it has.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_Optimize_for_Google_SGE_and_Bing_Copilot\"><\/span>How to Optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. Create content that directly answers questions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Generative engines like direct answers. Start with question-based headers such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>What is local SEO<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>How to fix a crawl budget issue<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Why is canonicalization important<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Provide clear, concise answers in the first paragraph below each heading. Use bullet points or numbered lists where possible.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2. Use structured data to mark up your content<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Google SGE optimization depends on understanding your content&#8217;s structure. Use schema markup for:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>FAQs<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>How to content<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Product or service reviews<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Organization and author data<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Use tools like Schema.org, RankMath, or manual JSON LD to enhance your pages with rich metadata.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3. Improve topical depth across clusters<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>AI search engines pull from semantically related content. Build topical clusters that go deep, not wide. Link related articles internally. Ensure each article supports a single theme.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you write about content strategy, cluster related topics like keyword research, content briefs, AI content validation, and publishing workflows.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This builds a strong foundation for AI to understand and summarize your content.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4. Strengthen author credibility and site trust<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Generative AI favors sources with a clear identity and credibility. Strengthen your E E A T signals by:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Adding author bios with credentials<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Listing sources and outbound links to trusted pages<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Using HTTPS, contact pages, and business information<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updating outdated content to reflect current facts<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Bing Copilot in particular cites high trust domains more often than thin affiliate pages or UGC.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5. Track AI snippet visibility<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Currently, Google SGE does not always show referral data. But you can:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Monitor AI traffic behavior with tools like Microsoft Clarity or Hotjar<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use tools like Oncrawl, Surfer AI, or detailed GSC reports to spot nontraditional ranking changes<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Manually test if your pages are featured in AI blocks using Incognito search and Copilot prompts<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_Not_to_Do_in_the_AI_SEO_Era\"><\/span>What Not to Do in the AI SEO Era<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Do not keyword stuff or repeat phrases unnaturally<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Do not rely only on backlinks to get visibility<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Do not write vague intros that fail to deliver value up front<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Do not use AI tools to spin content without editing or fact checking<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>AI search does not reward fluff. It rewards clarity, context, and real information.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span>Conclusion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO in the AI era requires a mindset shift. It is not about ranking on page one\u2014it is about being featured inside the answer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot, you need to build clear, fact-driven, and well-structured content ecosystems. That means better topical clustering, precise on page formatting, consistent internal linking, and stronger trust signals.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The websites that adapt early will gain a huge advantage in visibility, traffic quality, and brand recognition. The rest will compete for crumbs below the fold.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is time to optimize for the future. Not just for search. But for the AI that runs it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Unsure how to adapt your SEO to Google SGE or Bing Copilot?<\/strong><br><strong>Contact us \u2014 we\u2019ll help you build an AI-ready SEO strategy that drives results.<\/strong><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>AI is no longer coming&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":329,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4,26],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-328","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-advice","category-seo"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v23.3 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>SEO in the Age of AI Search: How to Optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot &#8212; UM<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Stay ahead in the AI era \u2014 learn how to optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot. Discover key strategies for future-proof SEO in 2025.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"SEO in the Age of AI Search: How to Optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot &#8212; UM\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Stay ahead in the AI era \u2014 learn how to optimize for Google SGE and Bing Copilot. Discover key strategies for future-proof SEO in 2025.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/blog\/seo-in-the-age-of-ai-search-how-to-optimize-for-google-sge-and-bing-copilot\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"UM\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2025-06-06T09:55:01+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2025-06-06T11:00:15+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/um.marketing\/wp-content\/uploads\/